verses.text_plain: Let brotherly love continue.
verses.verse_html: 1Let brotherly love continue.

verses.text_plain: Be not forgetful to entertain strangers: for thereby some have entertained angels unawares.
verses.verse_html: 2Be not forgetful to entertain strangers: for thereby some have entertained angels unawares.

verses.text_plain: Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them; and them which suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body.
verses.verse_html: 3Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them; and them which suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body.

verses.text_plain: Marriage is honourable in all, and the bed undefiled: but whoremongers and adulterers God will judge.
verses.verse_html: 4Marriage is honourable in all, and the bed undefiled: but whoremongers and adulterers God will judge.

verses.text_plain: Let your conversation be without covetousness; and be content with such things as ye have: for he hath said, I will never leave thee, nor forsake thee.
verses.verse_html: 5Let your conversation be without covetousness; and be content with such things as ye have: for he hath said, I will never leave thee, nor forsake thee.

tokens.text: with such things as ye have

verses.text_plain: So that we may boldly say, The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me.
verses.verse_html: 6So that we may boldly say, The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me.

verses.text_plain: Remember them which have the rule over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God: whose faith follow, considering the end of their conversation.
verses.verse_html: 7Remember them which have the rule over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God: whose faith follow, considering the end of their conversation.

tokens.text: them which have the rule over

verses.text_plain: Jesus Christ the same yesterday, and to day, and for ever.
verses.verse_html: 8Jesus Christ the same yesterday, and to day, and for ever.

verses.text_plain: Be not carried about with divers and strange doctrines. For it is a good thing that the heart be established with grace; not with meats, which have not profited them that have been occupied therein.
verses.verse_html: 9Be not carried about with divers and strange doctrines. For it is a good thing that the heart be established with grace; not with meats, which have not profited them that have been occupied therein.

verses.text_plain: We have an altar, whereof they have no right to eat which serve the tabernacle.
verses.verse_html: 10We have an altar, whereof they have no right to eat which serve the tabernacle.

verses.text_plain: For the bodies of those beasts, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest for sin, are burned without the camp.
verses.verse_html: 11For the bodies of those beasts, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest for sin, are burned without the camp.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people with his own blood, suffered without the gate.
verses.verse_html: 12Wherefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people with his own blood, suffered without the gate.

verses.text_plain: Let us go forth therefore unto him without the camp, bearing his reproach.
verses.verse_html: 13Let us go forth therefore unto him without the camp, bearing his reproach.

verses.text_plain: For here have we no continuing city, but we seek one to come.
verses.verse_html: 14For here have we no continuing city, but we seek one to come.

verses.text_plain: By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of our lips giving thanks to his name.
verses.verse_html: 15By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of our lips giving thanks to his name.

verses.text_plain: But to do good and to communicate forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.
verses.verse_html: 16But to do good and to communicate forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.

verses.text_plain: Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves: for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy, and not with grief: for that is unprofitable for you.
verses.verse_html: 17Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves: for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy, and not with grief: for that is unprofitable for you.

tokens.text: them that have the rule over

verses.text_plain: Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly.
verses.verse_html: 18Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly.

verses.text_plain: But I beseech you the rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.
verses.verse_html: 19But I beseech you the rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.

verses.text_plain: Now the God of peace, that brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the everlasting covenant,
verses.verse_html: 20Now the God of peace, that brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the everlasting covenant,

verses.text_plain: Make you perfect in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is wellpleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ; to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
verses.verse_html: 21Make you perfect in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is wellpleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ; to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.

verses.text_plain: And I beseech you, brethren, suffer the word of exhortation: for I have written a letter unto you in few words.
verses.verse_html: 22And I beseech you, brethren, suffer the word of exhortation: for I have written a letter unto you in few words.

verses.text_plain: Know ye that our brother Timothy is set at liberty; with whom, if he come shortly, I will see you.
verses.verse_html: 23Know ye that our brother Timothy is set at liberty; with whom, if he come shortly, I will see you.

verses.text_plain: Salute all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints. They of Italy salute you.
verses.verse_html: 24Salute all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints. They of Italy salute you.

tokens.text: them that have the rule over

verses.text_plain: Grace be with you all. Amen. Written to the Hebrews from Italy by Timothy.
verses.verse_html: 25Grace be with you all. Amen. Written to the Hebrews from Italy by Timothy.
